<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 07 at 4:13PM CDT  by NWS Bismarck</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT PORTIONS OF CENTRAL WARD, SOUTH
CENTRAL RENVILLE AND EAST CENTRAL MOUNTRAIL COUNTIES THROUGH 445 PM
CDT...
At 412 PM CDT, a strong thunderstorm was located 10 miles north of
Plaza, or 25 miles southeast of Stanley, moving northeast at 55 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts to 55 mph and nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Berthold around 425 PM CDT.
Des Lacs around 430 PM CDT.
Other locations in the path of this storm include Carpio and Foxholm.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
